cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SY 

The paper proposes a novel transformation of the caching optimization problem to a grey-scale image that is applied to a deep convolutional neural network (CNN). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) which deals with the development and application of neural networks and evolutionary algorithms. The paper also uses CNNs which are commonly used in computer vision, hence cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with optimization and decision making, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper proposes a data-driven approach, which could also fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
